27:21.373 --> 27:23.546
We'll figure it out.

27:24.877 --> 27:28.825
We need money... money we don't have.

27:31.483 --> 27:33.320
My cousin went.

27:33.385 --> 27:36.696
Guy charged her 250 bucks.

27:40.092 --> 27:42.429
Could you ask Mr. Kellerman for an advance?

27:42.494 --> 27:44.064
For this? Yeah, sure.

27:44.129 --> 27:46.300
He's just aching for a reason to fire us.

27:48.167 --> 27:50.337
Johnny, I'm scared.

27:50.402 --> 27:52.773
What if it starts to show?

27:52.838 --> 27:55.309
- I'll help you.
- This is none of your business.

27:55.374 --> 27:56.375
She's just trying to help.

27:56.442 --> 27:58.812
And thanks for coming to get me.
You did your good deed for the day.

27:58.877 --> 28:00.982
Now why don't you waltz on back
to the ballroom?

28:24.770 --> 28:26.340
Where are you going?

28:26.405 --> 28:28.942
Uh, nowhere. Go to sleep.

28:29.007 --> 28:31.378
Please tell me it's not to see our waiter.

28:31.443 --> 28:33.781
Come on, Baby, you're 18. Time to grow up.

28:33.846 --> 28:36.050
I just think there's more
to life than getting married.

28:36.115 --> 28:38.852
Why can't I just get married
without you judging me?

28:38.917 --> 28:41.555
Let's just accept the fact
that we have nothing in common.

28:41.620 --> 28:44.465
If we weren't sisters, we'd never be friends.

28:58.003 --> 29:00.140
Oh, thank you.

29:00.205 --> 29:02.481
You're so nice.

29:03.776 --> 29:08.885
A toast to the most beautiful girl
at Kellerman's.

29:11.250 --> 29:14.788
- Robbie.
- It's true.

29:14.853 --> 29:17.527
You're exactly the kind of girl
I dream about marrying someday.

29:19.725 --> 29:21.328
When is someday?

29:21.393 --> 29:23.831
I don't know. You tell me.

29:24.796 --> 29:26.536
What does that mean?

29:28.033 --> 29:29.103
Let me take this.

29:33.839 --> 29:36.510
I think...

29:36.575 --> 29:39.750
that you are incredible.

29:41.013 --> 29:42.549
You do?

29:44.249 --> 29:45.888
I do.

29:53.792 --> 29:56.663
How do you like hearing those words?

29:56.728 --> 29:57.898
- "I do"?
- Mm.

29:57.963 --> 30:00.701
Hmm. I do.

30:00.766 --> 30:03.372
I do. I do.

30:15.714 --> 30:17.050
- Robbie, wait.
- Why?

30:17.115 --> 30:18.552
Wait.

30:18.617 --> 30:21.054
- But we love each other.
- Robbie, stop.

30:21.119 --> 30:23.090
- Shh.
- No, stop. I'm...

30:23.155 --> 30:25.192
Wait, I... stop it.

30:25.257 --> 30:26.960
Robbie, stop it!

30:27.025 --> 30:28.527
- No, Robbie!
- Oh!

30:28.594 --> 30:30.574
I said no, you jerk!

30:32.397 --> 30:33.867
What are you gonna do? Cry to daddy?

30:33.932 --> 30:36.170
- Come on, Lisa. Come back.
- Don't you dare follow me!

30:36.235 --> 30:37.671
I'm gonna go to Mr. Kellerman and tell him!

30:37.736 --> 30:39.272
Tell him what?

30:39.338 --> 30:42.276
You came after me, remember?

30:42.341 --> 30:44.753
You brought the wine.

30:48.947 --> 30:50.984
Don't ever speak to me again.

30:58.190 --> 31:01.762
- Robbie, you play golf?
- Yes, sir.

31:01.827 --> 31:06.166
My father always said he made more deals
on the golf course than in the boardroom.

31:06.231 --> 31:07.935
You should come play golf with me.

31:08.000 --> 31:10.378
I'm sure Robbie has lots
of responsibilities in the kitchen.

31:11.970 --> 31:13.140
She's right, Dr. Houseman.

31:13.205 --> 31:16.414
I have to, uh, inventory the pantry today.

31:22.281 --> 31:25.419
Lisa, you don't have to be so rude.

31:25.484 --> 31:27.321
He's not gonna be a waiter forever, you know.

31:27.386 --> 31:28.622
Why do you people think

31:28.687 --> 31:31.291
that just because
a guy goes to Harvard or Yale

31:31.356 --> 31:32.526
that means he's perfect?

31:32.591 --> 31:34.828
I mean, maybe he's an axe murderer.

31:34.893 --> 31:37.064
Are you saying our waiter's an axe murderer?

31:37.129 --> 31:41.568
No. I... don't know, but he could be.

31:41.633 --> 31:43.370
We would never know.

31:43.435 --> 31:47.816
She's right, Jake. We would never know.

31:56.548 --> 31:58.018
What?

31:58.083 --> 31:59.553
What's the deal? You've been letting me win?

31:59.618 --> 32:02.322
No. Not at all.

32:02.387 --> 32:03.866
What's bugging you, honey?

32:05.090 --> 32:07.027
Can I borrow some money from you?

32:07.092 --> 32:10.497
It's for a friend... I can't tell you why.

32:10.562 --> 32:11.836
Is it something illegal?

32:14.032 --> 32:15.135
No.

32:15.200 --> 32:17.471
Well, how much do you need?

32:17.536 --> 32:19.243
$250.

32:21.373 --> 32:23.677
Wow.

32:23.742 --> 32:25.512
That's a lot of money.

32:25.577 --> 32:29.249
I'll pay you back, but it's for something
really important, Dad.

32:29.314 --> 32:31.685
I need you to trust me on this.

32:31.750 --> 32:33.696
I do trust you, Baby.

32:36.188 --> 32:38.191
Thanks, Daddy.

32:40.492 --> 32:42.995
<i># When I'm alone #</i>

32:44.663 --> 32:48.304
<i># With no one to love me #</i>

32:49.368 --> 32:52.306
<i># And the tears start to fall #</i>

32:52.371 --> 32:56.443
<i># From my eyes #</i>

